The application of implantable ports in chemotherapy, blood transfusion, antibiotics, intravenous infusion of blood products, pain management, and other medical procedures underscores their versatility and necessity in modern healthcare systems. Hospitals, clinics, ambulatory surgical centres, dialysis centres, and other healthcare facilities are the primary end-users benefiting from the convenience and efficiency offered by implantable ports in treatment protocols.

